# =============================================================================
# ArXiv RAG Copilot - Docker Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
#
# This project supports two deployment modes:
#
# 1. DEVELOPMENT (ChromaDB - Embedded Vector Store)
#    - No external database required
#    - Fast startup, simple setup
#    - Best for local development and testing
#    - Use: docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d
#    - Config: Copy .env.dev.example to .env
#
# 2. PRODUCTION (PostgreSQL + pgvector)
#    - Scalable, persistent vector store
#    - ACID compliance, concurrent access
#    - Best for production deployments
#    - Use: docker compose up -d
#    - Config: Copy .env.prod.example to .env
#
# Quick Start:
# ------------
# For development:
#   cp .env.dev.example .env
#   docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d
#
# For production:
#   cp .env.prod.example .env
#   # Edit .env and change all default passwords!
#   docker compose up -d
#
# =============================================================================

# Choose your configuration:
# - Copy .env.dev.example for local development (ChromaDB)
# - Copy .env.prod.example for production (PostgreSQL + pgvector)

# For a list of all available environment variables, see the
# .env.dev.example and .env.prod.example files.
